FBIS4-54029 "dreas101_n_94003" FBIS-EAS-94-101 Daily Report 24 May 1994 Vietnam Authorities Release Detained Malay Fishing Boat Authorities Release Detained Malay Fishing Boat BK2405064894 Kuala Lumpur Voice of Malaysia in English 0600 GMT 24 May 94 BK2405064894 Kuala Lumpur Voice of Malaysia English BFN [Text] Soc Trang provincial authorities in southern Vietnam freed a Malaysian fishing vessel and its crew of 31 Thais and three Malaysians late yesterday. Malaysian Consul General in Ho Chi Minh City Mr. M.H. Arshad told reporters in Hanoi the crew and the boat can sail home today barring any further hitches. He said the boat owner had promised to the provincial authorities that he would settle the fines in full by Saturday at the earliest. The provincial authorities had fined the fishermen 108,000 ringgit after the Vietnamese Navy caught them fishing in Vietnam's territorial waters on 3 May. The boat owner -- who acted independently, bypassing diplomatic channels -- [words indistinct] 1,000 ringgit when he first arrived in Soc Trang to secure the release of his boat and crew.
